-- Russia’s Capital Group Buys GeoProMining’s Assets in Georgia
-- B y   H e l e n a   B e d w e l l
-- 2012-06-19T17:50:22Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-19/russia-s-capital-group-buys-geopromining-s-assets-in-georgia.html
Russian businessmen Dmitry Korzhev
and Dmitry Troitsky, bought copper ore and  gold mines  in the
former Soviet republic of  Georgia  from GeoProMining Ltd., for
$120 million, said a spokeswoman for the units that were sold.  The two businessmen bought GeoProMining’s AO Madneuli and
OOO Kvartsit units through their company Capital Group, Tamuna
Liluashvili, the units’ spokeswoman, said by phone today in
Tbilisi, the capital of Georgia.  Capital Group has already invested as much as $10 million
and appointed a new general director, Liluashvili said. The
mining companies employ 2,000 people, she said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Helena Bedwell in Tbilisi at 
 hbedwell@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
